==English==
{{wikipedia}}

===Etymology===

From Italian slang ''fugazi'', "fake"; perhaps also slang version of ''Fugacious'' derived from Latin ''fugax'', ''fugac-'', "ready to flee, flying", hence, fleeting, transitory

===Adjective===
{{en-adj-notcomp}}

# {{slang}} Artificial, [[fake]], false.  Can be in reference to a thing or a person.  If a person it is usually in reference to a [[superficial]] person.
# {{slang}} Something that has no substance.

==={{acronym}}===

'''Fugazi'''

# {{US}} A term coined in the Vietnam War by American troops standing for ''''F'''ucked '''U'''p, '''G'''ot '''A'''mbushed, '''Z'''ipped '''I'''n', denoting a difficult situation.  (Actually a [[backronym]].)

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia|Fugazi (band)}}
'''Fugazi'''

# An underground Washinton D.C band, who defined the [[post-hardcore]] genre in the early 1990s. Founding members include the [[Minor Threat]] vocalist, Ian MacKaye.

